### 2. Limit Access

**Why Limit Access?**
Limiting access ensures that only authorized users or processes can trigger the dynamic aspect loading and unloading. This prevents unauthorized modifications to the application's behavior.

**How to Limit Access?**
You can use Spring Security or other authentication mechanisms to control who can access the endpoints responsible for loading and unloading aspects.

#### Using Spring Security

First, configure Spring Security to protect your endpoints:

```java
import org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;
import org.springframework.security.config.annotation.web.builders.HttpSecurity;
import org.springframework.security.config.annotation.web.configuration.WebSecurityConfigurerAdapter;

@Configuration
public class SecurityConfig extends WebSecurityConfigurerAdapter {

    @Override
    protected void configure(HttpSecurity http) throws Exception {
        http
            .authorizeRequests()
                .antMatchers("/enable-aspect", "/disable-aspect").authenticated()
                .and()
            .formLogin()
                .loginPage("/login")
                .permitAll()
                .and()
            .logout()
                .permitAll();
    }
}
```

